expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2466</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:addr>#362</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-362.xml</fr:route><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>20</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>erct-001N</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>Suppose we have two centres of contraction <fr:tex>a,a':A</fr:tex> with <fr:tex>\chi _ \bullet \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } a = x</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>\chi '_ \bullet \colon \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } a'=x</fr:tex> as witnesses of contraction. To identify <fr:tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a, \chi _ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex> with <fr:tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a', \chi '_ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex>, we employ the <fr:link
href="erct-0035.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0035">covariant sum</fr:link> of each of the <fr:link
href="erct-001C.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001C">pointwise path object</fr:link> structures on <fr:tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } -=x</fr:tex> over the <fr:link
href="erct-0013.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0013">intrinsic path object</fr:link> structure on <fr:tex>A</fr:tex>, constructing an identification <fr:tex>p \colon  a = a'</fr:tex> followed by a homotopy <fr:tex>H  \colon   \mathopen {} \left ( \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _{a'} \right ) \mathclose {} _*^{ \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } -=x}  \chi _ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}   \sim   \chi '_ \bullet</fr:tex>. Fixing <fr:tex>z \colon  A</fr:tex>, we compute:</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block">      \begin {aligned}        \mathopen {} \left ( \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _{a'} \right ) \mathclose {} _*^{ \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } -=x}  \chi _ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}  z       &amp;=        \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _{a'} \right ) \mathclose {} _*^{-=z}  \chi _z        \\        &amp;=        \chi _{a'} ^{-1}   \cdot   \chi _z        \\        &amp;=  \chi '_z      \end {aligned}   </fr:tex>

  <fr:p>The first and second steps follow from general computation lemmas for transport, and the last step follows from the fact that <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> is a <fr:link
href="erct-001J.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001J">set</fr:link>, which we may deduce from <fr:ref
addr="erct-001K"
href="erct-001K.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref> and <fr:ref
addr="erct-001L"
href="erct-001L.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
